---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Basic Usage - Balinese Calendar" description="Common usage patterns for the Balinese Calendar crate">
	<h1 class="font-display text-4xl gold-accent mb-8">Basic Usage</h1>

	<p class="text-lg mb-6">
		This guide covers common usage patterns for the Balinese Calendar crate.
	</p>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-4">Creating Dates</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">From Gregorian Date</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use balinese_calendar::BalineseDate;

// Create from year, month, day
let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2026, 3, 25)?;</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">From Current Date</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use chrono::Local;
use balinese_calendar::BalineseDate;

let now = Local::now();
let today = BalineseDate::from_ymd(
    now.year(),
    now.month(),
    now.day()
)?;</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-4">Accessing Calendar Components</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Wewaran (Weekly Cycles)</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2026, 3, 25)?;

// 7-day week (like Sunday-Saturday)
println!("Saptawara: {}", date.saptawara());

// 5-day market week
println!("Pancawara: {}", date.pancawara());

// Other cycles
println!("Sadwara: {}", date.sadwara());    // 6-day
println!("Astawara: {}", date.astawara());  // 8-day
println!("Sangawara: {}", date.sangawara()); // 9-day
println!("Dasawara: {}", date.dasawara());  // 10-day</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Pawukon System</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">// Wuku (30 weeks in 210-day cycle)
println!("Wuku: {}", date.wuku_name());
println!("Pawukon day: {}", date.pawukon_day());</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Sasih (Lunar Calendar)</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">// Lunar month and year
println!("Sasih: {}", date.sasih_name());
println!("Saka Year: {}", date.saka_year());

// Check for intercalary month
if date.is_nampih() {
    println!("This is a Nampih (intercalary) month");
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-4">Working with Holy Days</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Finding Rahinan</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">// Check if there are any holy days
if !date.rahinan().is_empty() {
    println!("Holy days today:");
    for rahinan in date.rahinan() {
        println!("  - {:?}", rahinan);
    }
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-4">Error Handling</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Handling Invalid Dates</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use balinese_calendar::{BalineseDate, BalineseDateError};

match BalineseDate::from_ymd(2026, 2, 30) {
    Ok(date) => println!("Valid date"),
    Err(e) => eprintln!("Error: {}", e),
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Graceful Degradation</h3>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">// Process a range of dates, skipping invalid ones
for day in 1..=31 {
    if let Ok(date) = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2026, 2, day) {
        // Process valid date
        println!("Day {}: {}", day, date.wuku_name());
    }
    // Invalid dates (like Feb 30) are silently skipped
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-4">Next Steps</h2>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
		<li><a href="/balinese-calendar/guide/advanced-features" class="text-balinese-turquoise hover:text-balinese-gold">Advanced Features</a> for more complex use cases</li>
		<li><a href="/balinese-calendar/concepts/calendar-systems" class="text-balinese-turquoise hover:text-balinese-gold">Calendar Systems</a> to understand the concepts</li>
		<li><a href="/balinese-calendar/api/balinese-date" class="text-balinese-turquoise hover:text-balinese-gold">API Reference</a> for complete documentation</li>
	</ul>
</DocsLayout>
